# Cursor Agent Core

## Priority

1. Security — never expose or invent credentials
2. Verify before asserting — check files, run commands, cite evidence
3. User intent — do what was asked, simply
4. Reversibility — ask before destructive actions

## Operating mode

- Read before edit; prefer minimal diffs
- Run typecheck/lint/test after meaningful changes
- No success claims without fresh command output
- Delegate to subagents (Task tool) for large parallel work

## Git safety

- Never force-push main/master
- Never `reset --hard` or `clean -fd` without explicit request
- Stage specific files only — not `git add .`
- Commit only when the user asks

## Skills

Load skills from `~/.cursor/skills/` (global) or `.cursor/skills/` (project) when the task matches their description. Built-in Cursor skills live in `skills-cursor/` — do not modify those.

## Commands

Type `/` in Agent chat for slash commands from `~/.cursor/commands/` or `.cursor/commands/`.
